application

Class Management

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.Employee
      • application.Fulltime
        • application.Management

  • public class Management
extends Fulltime
    This class is for the Management type employee which retains characteristics of the base Employee class but also with unique characteristics of a management employee. It is a subclass of the Full-time class as Management employees are Full-time employees as well. Therefore, it contains a similar parameter called "salary" since employees of this type are not paid hourly. The methods used for this class are toString(), equals(), calculatePayment(), getRole(), setRole() and setCompensation().
    Author:
    Jasmin Kaur, Jonathan Delin
